# Contact Sharing

This feature allows members picking up their <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> at the same depot to share their contact information with each other. It can help build community and facilitate practical arrangements like carpooling or coordinating pickups.

## How It Works {#how-it-works}

Once this feature is activated in [your settings](/settings#organization_features_input), members can opt in to contact sharing from their account. The process is simple:

1. The member navigates to the "Contact Sharing" section in their account.
2. They accept the terms of service to confirm they agree to share their information.
3. Once opted in, they can see the name, phone number, and address of other members who have also opted in **at the same depot for the same delivery**.

Each member only sees others who pick up at the same depot — not all members of the organization. The list updates automatically based on the next upcoming delivery.

> Contact sharing is entirely voluntary. Members who don't opt in remain invisible to others, and their information is never shared.

## Opting Out {#opting-out}

Members who wish to stop sharing their contact information need to contact the organization. An administrator can then disable contact sharing for that member from their profile.

## Privacy {#privacy}

- **Scope is limited** – only members at the same depot for the same delivery can see each other.
- **Opt-in only** – no information is shared until a member explicitly agrees.
- **GDPR compliant** – contact sharing preferences are cleared when a member's account is [anonymized](/handbook/right_to_be_forgotten).

> No additional configuration is needed beyond enabling the feature. There are no settings to adjust, it's a simple on/off toggle for the organization.
